 Old English form <i>Hrōðgār</i>. <i>Roger</i> was one of the most popular boys' names throughout the medieval period, but less so after the Reformation, though it has continued in regular use to the present day.  Roger, Count of Sicily  (  <i>c.</i>1031–1101 ), son of Tancred, recovered Sicily from the Arabs. His son, also called Roger, ruled Sicily as king, presiding over a court noted for its splendour and patronage of the arts."],"variants":[{"name":"Rodger","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Roger  , in part from the surname derived from the given name in the Middle Ages."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Roger de Waure was born in 1204, in Eccleshall, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom as the son of John De Waure. He had at least 1 daughter. He died in England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1204–":"1204–Surnud","1204–Male":"1204–Surnud","1240–1290":"1240–1290","1186–1251":"1186–1251","1204":"1204","1186":"1186","1251":"1251","1240":"1240","1290":"1290","Eccleshall, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Eccleshall, Staffordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1204–":"1204–Kuollut","1204–Male":"1204–Kuollut","1240–1290":"1240–1290","1186–1251":"1186–1251","1204":"1204","1186":"1186","1251":"1251","1240":"1240","1290":"1290","Eccleshall, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Eccleshall, Staffordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1204–":"1204–Décédé","1204–Male":"1204–Décédé","1240–1290":"1240–1290","1186–1251":"1186–1251","1204":"1204","1186":"1186","1251":"1251","1240":"1240","1290":"1290","Eccleshall, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Eccleshall, Staffordshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","England":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Roger de Waure est né en 1204, à Eccleshall, Staffordshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, fils de John De Waure. Il a eu au moins 1 fille. Il est décédé à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni."},"de":{"1204–":"1204–Verstorben","1204–Male":"1204